description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a motivated, inspiring, well-organised and committed midwife to support midwifery students in practice at North West Anglia, NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a pivotal role to support pre-registration midwifery education. The focus of this role is to support student midwives in practice by working alongside them in clinical practice; support supervisors and assessors and be influential in improving the quality of the clinical learning environment, further enhancing student experience and developing our future workforce.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be a registered Midwife who is passionate about nurturing and developing others. You must have exceptional communication skills and be a visible and credible role model for all levels of staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role involves assisting with the facilitation of training, education and support of the practice and professional development of all pre-registration midwifery students in practice ensuring that they meet the NMC standards for pre-registration education.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an influential role, requiring persistence, diplomacy and vision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name   Helen Hutchings&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title   Assistant Director of Nursing- Non Medical Education&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address   helen.hutchings2@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
